1.  disable USB autosuspend
   -edit /boot/extlinux/extlinux.conf
   -add 'usbcore.autosuspend=-1' to modify the line 'APPEND ${cbootargs} usbcore.autosuspend=-1 quiet'

2.  add user to dialout group to enable serial port access
   -sudo adduser jseng dialout

3.  disable auto updates of packages
   -edit /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/10periodic

4.  add the external SSD to /etc/fstab using:
   UUID=de8a2a2f-13c4-4662-a1de-9697d5ce74e8   /mnt/temp   ext4 defaults 0  0

   -change the UUID to the correct one (find the correct one by running 'ls -al /dev/disk/by-uuid/')

